rComments: One of the best profs I've ever had!
What an eloquent, extremely knowledgeable prof. She was so interested in what she was teaching and she made everything very engaging. I would take another course of hers because of her fine teaching.
Great prof, explains clearly and keeps things interesting!
An amazing and inspiring professor. Delivers information in a coherent manner. Also includes the contemporary history and criticism of works we have studied. Extremely friendly and accessible.
Very friendly and engaging. The lectures are enjoyable.

One of the best profs I've ever had, and THE most articulate person I've ever met. Knowledgeable, kind, helpful, and very professional. The course was a joy...I went into it thinking I would hate CanLit and now I want to do my Master's dissertation on it.
aware of students needs and concerns. very approachable and understanding
Enthusiastic, knowledgable, approachable, flexible, and always prepared, Darroch is one of the best profs in the department.  Her class was simply fantastic.

Darroch is an enthusiastic professor whose care and concern for her students is quite genuine.  She always greets her classes with a smile and goes out of her way to make each of her students feel appreciated and important.  I loved her class.
Quite approachable, open-minded, and knowledgable!  This course was a pleasure!
